<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 5: ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT
        ASSEMBLY, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - CAMSHAFT ASSEMBLY - ASSEMBLY OF CAMGEAR ONTO CAMSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ASSEMBLY OF CAMGEAR ONTO CAMSHAFT</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>HEATING A CAMSHAFT GEAR BEYOND 177&#176;C (350&#176; F) WILL CAUSE IT TO TURN
                        <emph type="underscr">BLUE</emph>.
                        <emph type="underscr">ANY CAMSHAFT GEAR WHICH HAS TURNED BLUE CANNOT BE REUSED.</emph>
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                <emph type="underscr">IF ONLY</emph>
                the camgear was removed, perform the following:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Heat the camshaft gear in an oven to 149-177&#176; C (300-350&#176; F).</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>1. BE SURE TO USE WELDING GLOVES.</para>
                        <para>2. CAMSHAFT GEAR SHOULD SLIDE ONTO CAMSHAFT WITH SLIGHT HAND PRESSURE.
                            <emph type="underscr">DO NOT</emph>
                            FORCE CAMGEAR.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Use welding gloves to install the heated camshaft gear. Remove camgear assembly from
                    oven.
                    <emph type="underscr">BE SURE</emph>
                    to align the camgear timing marks with the upper idler gear and install onto camshaft with timing
                    marks showing.
                    <emph type="underscr">HOLD</emph>
                    camshaft gear on camshaft until it tightens as it cools (approximately 30 seconds,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_123.xml" xrefid="ef1600524">5.24</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
